summary: This document is a cover sheet for FBI evidence migration, referencing two attachments: an FD-26 consent to search form signed by Alfredo Rodriguez and an FD-395 form also signed by Alfredo Rodriguez. It indicates the FBI acquired these items on November 6, 2009.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: He signed both the FD-26 consent to search form and an FD-395 form, which were acquired by the FBI as part of an evidence package.

events.title: FBI acquisition of consent forms
events.description: The FBI acquired a package containing a consent to search form (FD-26) and another form (FD-395), both signed by Alfredo Rodriguez.

keyFacts: Alfredo Rodriguez signed an FD-26 consent to search form, indicating he permitted a search by law enforcement.
Alfredo Rodriguez also signed an FD-395 form, which is typically a receipt for property taken by the FBI.
These signed documents were acquired by the FBI on November 6, 2009, and were part of a serial evidence package.
